2 Definitions.—1[***] In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—
a “article” means an article of the Constitution;
b “Assembly constituency” means a constituency provided
2[by law] for the purpose of elections to the Legislative Assembly of a State;
c “Council constituency” means a constituency provided
3[by law] for the purpose of elections to the Legislative Council of a State;
4[***]
d “Election Commission” means the Election Commission appointed by the President under article 324;
e “order” means an order published in the Official Gazette;
f “parliamentary constituency” means a constituency provided
5[by law] for the purpose of elections to the House of the People;
6[***]
g “person” does not include a body of persons;
h “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;
7[(i) “State” includes a Union territory;]
j “State Government”, in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof.
